{
  "texts": [
    "It is also important to consider that the computation time and resources required in ICL can increase with the number of examples used 34.",
    "Additionally, we note that LLMs integrate information from the example ICL cases, which compromises the report quality as well as patient privacy (Supplemental Table 4).",
    "While this behavior was not reported in other studies 13, 34, we believe it could be a common condition, that is easier to identify with numerical values (in echo) compared to narrative statements (in CXR).",
    "Therefore, even in scenarios where ICL can outperform fine-tuning 13, fine-tuning may be preferable.",
    "The EchoGen study previously demonstrated that BART and other rule-based approaches are effective for summarizing echocardiogram reports, with BART achieving ROUGE-based scores between 0.65 and 0.73 26."
  ]
}